document_data.History:
The Palace was built over the ruins of an abbey dedicated to [[Chauntea]] that was destroyed during the [[Trollwars#Second_Trollwar|Second Trollwar]] in the mid–10{{th}} century [[DR]]. In the 1370s, relatively harmless [[ghost]]s of Chauntean monks and clerics could still be seen occasionally roaming halls and staircases that no longer existed, passing through the walls of the modern-day castle.{{Cite web/Realms by Night/Part Six: The Monks of the Three Candles}}

The construction and instillation of 'Timehands' was completed in the {{YearlinkName|1445}}.

The four meetings of the [[Council of Waterdeep]] were hosted in the Lords' Palace some time during the 1480s DR.{{ToD-time}}
